<text top="71" left="772" width="647" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t64" reading_order_no="63" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">sporadic  skirmishing.  That,  and  the </text>
<text top="115" left="771" width="648" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t65" reading_order_no="64" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">week’s  long  string  of  northern  defeats, </text>
<text top="159" left="772" width="649" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t66" reading_order_no="65" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">convinced  anti-Taliban  Pashtun  that  they </text>
<text top="202" left="772" width="647" height="52" font="font1" id="p1_t67" reading_order_no="66" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">could  take  down  the  core  Taliban  war- </text>
<text top="246" left="771" width="648" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t68" reading_order_no="67" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">riors  in  the  south  and  persuade  the  rest  to </text>
<text top="290" left="772" width="648" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t69" reading_order_no="68" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">switch  sides;  the  prospect  of  Tajik,  Uzbek </text>
<text top="335" left="772" width="647" height="49" font="font2" id="p1_t70" reading_order_no="69" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">and  Hazara  fighters  sweeping  into  Pash- </text>
<text top="378" left="771" width="648" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t71" reading_order_no="70" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">tun  cities  was  far  more  harrowing  to  Tal- </text>
<text top="422" left="772" width="647" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t72" reading_order_no="71" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">iban  soldiers  than  was  surrendering  to </text>
<text top="466" left="771" width="366" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t73" reading_order_no="72" segment_no="1" tag_type="text">their  Pashtun  brothers. </text>
<text top="511" left="834" width="586" height="49" font="font2" id="p1_t74" reading_order_no="73" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">Outside  Kandahar,  some  anti-Taliban </text>
