<text top="690" left="1696" width="423" height="46" font="font6" id="p1_t101" reading_order_no="102" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">linked  to  the  opium  trade, </text>
<text top="731" left="1695" width="425" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t102" reading_order_no="103" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">would  both  become  inter- </text>
<text top="775" left="1696" width="424" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t103" reading_order_no="104" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">im  leaders  of  Kandahar.  Ac- </text>
<text top="818" left="1696" width="424" height="51" font="font4" id="p1_t104" reading_order_no="105" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">cording  to  sources  in  the </text>
<text top="866" left="1696" width="425" height="46" font="font6" id="p1_t105" reading_order_no="106" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">city,  a  distraught  Omar,  at </text>
<text top="906" left="1696" width="424" height="50" font="font1" id="p1_t106" reading_order_no="107" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">times  on  the  verge  of weep- </text>
<text top="949" left="1696" width="423" height="51" font="font4" id="p1_t107" reading_order_no="108" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">ing,  met  briefly  with  the </text>
